     Vugraphs for invited papers will be posted on the ITC 12 conference
   web site and all papers will be published. Vugraphs and papers of
   specific interest to FIRE have been collected and are posted below.
     * FIRE, Exploring the Frontiers of Burning Plasma Science D. Meade
       (1.8MB, pdf) and paper D. Meade (170 kB, pdf)
     * D-T Experiments R. Hawryluk (1.1 MB, pdf)
     * Resistive Wall Mode Control on the DIII-D Device M. Okabayashi et
       al (13.5 MB, pdf)
     * Confinement and Heating Studies on the National Spherical Torus
       Experiment (NSTX) E. Synakowski et al (3.5 MB, pdf)
     * Laboratory Study of Plasma Space/Astrophysics: Magnetic
       Reconnection and Magneto-Rotational Instability H. Ji (1.6 MB, pdf)
     * Stellarator Fusion Reactors - An Overview H. Wobig, paper (72 kB,
       pdf)
     * First Island Divertor Experiments on the W7-AS Stellarator W P.
       Grigull (1.3 M, pdf)
     * High Performance Operational Limits of Tokamak and Helical Systems
       P. Yamazaki (1.1 M, pdf)
     * Study of Time Evolution of Toroidal Current in LHD K. Watanabe (1
       MB, pdf)F
     * ITER Confinement and Stability Modeling A. R. Polevoi (216 kB, pdf)
     * Divertor Requirements and Performance in ITER M. Sugihara (252 kB,
       pdf)
     * Global Power Balance in Long Duration Discharges in TRIAM-1M M.
       Sakamoto (1.3 MB, pdf)F
     * Fusion Technology R & D in Japan A. Kohyama (2.8 MB, pdf)
     * Status of the KSTAR Project Status of the KSTAR Project and Fusion
       Research in Korea G. S. Lee (1.6 MB, pdf)
     * Magnetic Confinement Fusion Research in China by Yuan xi Wan (pdf)
          + Part 1 (1.1 MB), Part 2 (3.1 MB), Part 3 (2.4 MB), Part 4 (1.4
            MB), Part 5 (1.7 MB)
     * Status of SST-1 Project and Fusion Research in India Y. Saxena (3.9
       MB, pdf)
     * Comparison of the Fusion with Other Prospective Energy Sources K.
       Okano (284 kB, pdf)Fu

